{
  "doc_id": "3287",
  "text": "Finally, validation of possible phenotypes using longitudinal outcomes was performed only in a limited number of studies: Burgel et al. performed two studies in two different cohorts of COPD outpatients and validated their findings using all-cause mortality [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Garcia-Aymerich et al. studied patients recruited at the time of a first hospitalization for COPD exacerbation and used all-cause mortality and hospitalizations related to COPD and to cardiovascular diseases to validate their findings [CITATION_4] . Altenburg et al. found two phenotypes in which patients responded differently to pulmonary rehabilitation [CITATION_5] . Other studies did not report prospective validation of their findings. At the end, although these limitations should be taken into consideration, cluster analyses have resulted in interesting preliminary results that are summarized in the next section.",
